dct_description_sm: Map shows major buildings and facilities, cemeteries, mosques and churches, and gurgis (mud huts). "Compiled from miscellaneous information up to January, 1959. Edition 2 revised from information supplied by HQ BFAP dated 1960. UTM grid added by SPC RE 1968." "Blue numbered lines indicate the 100 metre Universal transverse Mercator Grid Zone 38 Clarke 1880 Spheroid. The last two digits of the Grid numbers are omitted." "Printed by SPC RE 1/70/1628/SPC." "NIMA ref. no. Y921XHARGEISA." "NSN 7643014045158." ©Crown copyright 1970 "Universal Transverse Mercator grid, zone 38."
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. Directorate of Military Survey
dct_publisher_sm: United Kingdom : D Survey, Ministry of Defence, 1970.
Bethesda, MD : National Imagery and Mapping Agency, 2000.
